<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.85.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">idea on ilo</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/idea/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/idea/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/idea/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-07-12T04:56:11+00:00</updated><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/idea/</id><entry><title type="html">Editors</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/contributors/editors/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/contributors/editors/</id><published>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="intellij">IntelliJ</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/">IntelliJ Idea</a> is a popular IDE by <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/">Jetbrains</a>. It allows <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/sharing-your-ide-settings.html">several ways</a> to share settings across team members in a project.</p>
<p><code>ilo</code> stores its IntelliJ settings inside its <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/creating-and-managing-projects.html#share-project-through-vcs">git repository</a> and thus should work out-of-the-box for other IntelliJ users.</p>
<p>In case you have trouble getting <code>ilo</code> to work in IntelliJ, take a look at the <a href="../../community/help">help</a> section.</p>
